If you are ok to go with width binding approach, then you can try the below approach to hide the horizontal scroll bar. And yes, this will need some extra class/code,. but will help you to have a better control on other things (if required).

The hBar visibility and the other row positioning logic is in the `layoutChildren` method of `VirtualFlow`. So the idea is to tweak some changes for this part of logic in the `layoutChildren` method of `VirtualFlow`. And for this, you need to create a customized VirtualFlow, which eventually leads to creating custom skin and tableView.

So the code will be as simple as :

    class CustomTableView&lt;K&gt; extends TableView&lt;K&gt; {
        @Override
        protected Skin&lt;?&gt; createDefaultSkin() {
            return new CustomTableViewSkin&lt;&gt;(this);
        }
    }
    
