`allMatch()` is a short-circuiting function, so you can use it to stop processing. 

The main disadvantage is that you have to do your test twice: once to see if you should process it, and again to see whether to keep going.

And also, this solution returns a Boolean so you cannot collect the results of the stream as you normally would, but maybe it will work for you in this case.

     boolean result = authors.stream()
                .flatMap(author -&gt; author.getBooks().stream())
                .mapToInt(book -&gt; 1)
